# 2. Findings page

## Purpose

This should become the flagship screen of the whole product.

## Layout

Three-pane default layout:

* left: findings list with powerful filters
* center: finding detail and evidence
* right or bottom: code viewer and flow inspector

Alternative layout toggle:

* list + full width detail
* list + split code
* full code-focused investigation mode

## Findings list

Columns should be configurable. Default columns:

* severity
* confidence
* rule id
* title
* category
* file
* line
* status
* scan

Filters should include:

* severity
* confidence
* category
* language
* rule
* path or directory
* status
* only new
* only changed
* only triaged
* only unsuppressed
* scan scope

Search should support:

* file name
* rule id
* function name
* sink name
* free text

Bulk actions:

* suppress selected
* mark false positive
* accept risk
* export selected
* add label

## Finding detail panel

This should include sections, not one monolithic card.

### Section: Summary

* title
* severity
* confidence
* category
* CWE if applicable
* language
* file and line
* first seen / last seen
* status

### Section: Why Nyx reported this

This is essential.

Show:

* matched rule
* source
* sink
* whether sanitizer was missing or bypassed
* path length
* branch notes if path-sensitive analysis exists
* assumptions made
* interprocedural summary use if relevant

### Section: Evidence

Examples:

* `req.query.id` recognized as source
* value flowed through `buildCommand()`
* call to `exec()` matched sink model
* no configured sanitizer on the path

### Section: Confidence reasoning

Explain how the confidence was determined in plain technical language.

For example:

* direct source to sink path
* no unresolved calls on path
* known sink match
* no sanitizer hit
* high certainty because path remained feasible

This should not be a black box label.

### Section: Triage controls

Actions:

* suppress this result
* suppress this fingerprint
* suppress by rule in file
* mark false positive
* mark accepted risk
* add note
* assign state label

### Section: Related findings

Show nearby or same-rule findings in same file or call chain.

## Code viewer

When a finding is selected, the code viewer should:

* open exact file and line
* syntax highlight
* highlight source node
* highlight sink node
* optionally highlight intermediate flow nodes
* show inline markers in gutter
* allow keyboard nav between findings
* allow jump to previous and next node in flow

Extra modes:

* source only
* sink only
* full path overlay
* surrounding function
* surrounding class or module

## Flow inspector

This is the biggest differentiator.

Should support:

* ordered source-to-sink flow list
* collapsible step cards
* per-step file and line
* per-step code snippet
* notes on transformations
* sanitizer checks
* argument and return transitions

Optional advanced modes:

* graph view
* timeline view
* function-by-function stacked view

