## Data model and backend capabilities the UI will need

To support this UI well, the backend should expose structured concepts, not just flat findings rows.

## Finding object should ideally include

* id or stable fingerprint
* title
* rule id
* category
* severity
* confidence
* file path
* line and column
* language
* message
* code snippet
* source nodes
* sink nodes
* flow steps
* sanitizer steps
* related symbol names
* explanation text or explanation fragments
* confidence reasons
* triage state
* first seen / last seen
* scan ids

## Scan object should include

* scan metadata
* timing breakdown
* config profile
* engine version
* files scanned
* files skipped
* metrics
* artifacts

## Rule object should include

* metadata
* language scope
* category
* severity default
* custom or built-in flag
* match logic or rule config
* sources / sinks / sanitizers
* example findings
* stats

## Debug artifacts should include

* CFG data
* SSA data
* call graph edges
* taint graph nodes and edges
* path decisions
* summary information

Without structured backend data, the UI will always feel shallow.

